        <h2 style="text-align: center">REFUND POLICY</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content">
        <h4>1. Conditions Apply</h4>
        <p>
          Subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Returns and
          Refund Policy and forming part of the Terms of Service, Aladin
          protects the interests of Buyers by allowing product return requests
          and /or refund before expiration. The term Aladin Guarantee has been
          set forth in the Terms of Service. Aladin Guarantees performed by
          Aladin, at the request of the User, to assist the User in resolving
          conflicts that may arise during the transaction. Users can contact
          each other to agree on the resolution of their dispute or report to
          Aladin or a competent state agency for assistance in resolving any
          dispute that occurs before, during or after using Aladin Guarantee.
          Return and/or refund policy for Aladin Mall products is set forth in
          Aladin Mall Terms of Service.
        </p>
        <h4>2. Return/Refund Request Conditions</h4>
        <p>
          Buyer agrees that she/he may request a return/refund only in the
          following cases: The buyer has paid but (i) did not receive the
          products, or (ii) did not receive all the ordered products, or (iii)
          received the products that are counterfeit or imitation goods;
          Products are defective or damaged during transit; Seller delivers
          wrong product to Buyer (e.g. wrong size, wrong color, etc.); The
          Product the Buyer receives is markedly different from the information
          provided by the Seller in the product description; The returned
          Product is not a Restricted Return Product; The Seller has reached an
          agreement and agreed to the Buyer to return the goods (however Aladin
          will need the Seller to confirm these agreements).
        </p>
        <p>
          Buyers can submit a return/refund request within 07 (seven) days (for
          products belonging to Aladin Mall) and 03 (three) days (for products
          not belonging to Aladin Mall) from the time the order is placed. Item
          has been updated and delivered successfully. Particularly for fresh
          and frozen food products (unless they have not yet been received),
          Buyers need to submit a return/refund request within 24 hours from the
          time the order is updated.
        </p>
        <h4>3. No Mind Changing</h4>
        <p>
          Except as mentioned in this Returns and Refunds Policy, returns due to
          Buyer's change of mind will not be accepted.
        </p>
        <h4>4. Seller's Rights</h4>
        <p>
          Upon receipt of a return and/or refund request from Buyer, Aladin will
          review and decide for Buyer to be returned/refunded, and notify (i) of
          his/her return/refund request. Buyer or (ii) decides to process Aladin
          Return/Refund request to Seller on App and/or email and/or text
          message. Seller needs to give feedback within 02 calendar days (or
          other time limit specified by Aladin from time to time) from the date
          of receipt of Aladin's notice if they disagree with Aladin's refund
          decision or have not yet received it. Returned goods/returned goods do
          not fall under the circumstances in which the Buyer is entitled to a
          refund/return or the goods are damaged or lost during the return
          process. After this time, if Aladin does not receive any response from
          the Seller, Aladin understands that the Seller fully agrees with
          Aladin's handling decision and has no complaints. Refund to the Buyer
          may be considered by Aladin without the Buyer having to return the
          item to the Seller.
        </p>
        <h4>5. Condition of The Returned item</h4>
        <p>
          In order to limit the arising problems related to returns, Buyers note
          that they need to pack according to the regulations on packaging of
          goods in Aladin Shipping Policy and return the product including all
          accompanying accessories, VAT invoice, warranty stamp (if any) and the
          product must be in the same condition as when received. Buyers are
          required to take a video or take photos of the product immediately
          upon receipt and during the packaging of the returned item as proof of
          comparison/complaint later.
        </p>
        <h4>6. Returning Costs</h4>
        <p>
          6.1. With goods purchased at Aladin Mall, Buyers can choose to return:
          In the form of “Return at home” or “Deliver at the post office”:
          Buyers do not have to pay any shipping fees for the return; In the
          form of "Self-arranged": The buyer needs to pay the shipping cost for
          the return in advance. Aladin will refund the amount equal to the
          shipping amount paid by the Buyer to the carrier through the “Aladin
          Account Balance” on the Aladin app within 3-5 working days from the
          date the Buyer has Return the item to the carrier and Buyer's
          return/refund request is accepted. 6.2. For goods not belonging to
          Aladin Mall, Buyers can choose to return the goods: In the form of
          "Return at home" or "Return at the post office": Buyer does not have
          to pay any shipping fees for the return. In the form of
          "Self-arranged": The buyer needs to pay the shipping cost for the
          return in advance. Aladin will support a partial refund of the return
          fee in the form of Aladin Coins according to Aladin's policy when the
          Buyer meets the conditions for support within 3-5 working days from
          the date the Buyer has sent Return the item to the carrier and Buyer's
          return/refund request is accepted
        </p>
        <h4>7. Refund for Returned Goods</h4>
        <p>
          7.1. Aladin will only refund Buyer when Buyer meets one of the
          following conditions: (i) Seller acknowledges receipt of Returned
          Goods, or (ii) Buyer accepts the offer of no return refund of the
          Seller, or (iii) the Buyer's Order is eligible for a return/refund and
          Aladin determines to the Buyer a refund when the Buyer has returned
          the item to the carrier and the carrier confirms Received have
          received the returned item. 7.2. In the event that the Buyer has no
          history of violating Aladin's policies and community standards, Aladin
          will in some cases decide to immediately refund the Buyer without
          having to wait for the Buyer to return the goods or respond. the cases
          specified in Article 7.1 above. 7.3. Aladin will automatically refund
          the Buyer in case the Seller does not respond within the pre-specified
          time period. For more information on Seller response deadlines, please
          click here. For more information on refunds, please click here. 7.4.
          As the case may be, the refund will be credited to the Aladin Account
          Balance, AladinPay Wallet, or the Buyer's credit/debit card registered
          with Aladin.
        </p>

        7.5. For cases of immediate refund proposed by the Seller, the refund
        amount will be mutually agreed upon by the two Parties but must not be
        less than 50% of the value of the product for which the return/refund
        request arises. In case Aladin receives a claim from the Buyer for the
        reason that the Seller refund is less than 50% of the product value,
        Aladin, at any time, has the right to deduct from the Seller's Aladin
        Account Balance No. the difference (determined as 100% of the product
        value minus the amount refunded to the Buyer) to pay the Buyer without
        notice or consent of the Seller. This regulation is intended to prevent
        profiteering and ensure the transparency and fairness of Aladin's Return
        and Refund Policy.
        <h4>8. Communication Between Seller and Buyer</h4>
        <p>
          Aladin encourages Buyers to actively contact the Seller to negotiate
          and resolve with each other through the communication channels
          provided on the Aladin system when there are any problems arising in
          the transaction.
        </p>
        <h4>9. Dispute Between Buyer and Seller</h4>
        <p>
          In the event that the Buyer and the Seller cannot agree on a solution,
          the Buyer and the Seller can complain about this to the Authorities
          for settlement. If one party complains to the other party to the
          authorities, the complaining party should promptly notify Aladin of
          this dispute together with the requested information from Aladin that
          Aladin considers reasonable, on a case-by-case basis. specific job. In
          that case, Seller and Buyer mutually agree that once Aladin has
          received notice and information related to the dispute, when the goods
          have not been paid to Seller in accordance with Aladin's regulations
          Assured, Aladin reserves the right to suspend payment to Seller until
          a final decision is made on the settlement of a dispute between Seller
          and Buyer. In the event that this payment has been paid to the Seller
          in accordance with the Aladin Guarantee policy, both Buyer and Seller
          agree that Aladin is no longer responsible for resolving any claim,
          dispute between the two parties or there is no longer any any
          responsibility for the goods. Buyer and Seller agree to indemnify and
          hold Aladin harmless, or against, against any claim, action, or other
          obligations/liability, damages, claims, penalties, fines, costs and
          expenses (including, without limitation, any other dispute resolution
          costs) arising out of or in connection with any action by Aladin under
          the Returns and Refunds Policy. this money.
        </p>
